is (Asian Affairs Journal)]\n*[http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/middle_east/country_profiles/1706450.stm Timeline: Yemen (BBC)]\n*[https://news.vice.com/article/as-saudis-block-a-human-rights-inquiry-in-yemen-the-us-stays-quiet As Saudis Block a Human Rights Inquiry in Yemen, America Stays Quiet]. ''[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]].'' 1 October 2015.\n*[https://www.hrw.org/news/2015/12/21/yemen-coalition-bombs-homes-capital Yemen: Coalition Bombs Homes in Capital]. [[Human Rights Watch]]. 21 December 2015.\n*[https://www.thenation.com/article/the-united-states-may-be-guilty-of-war-crimes-in-yemen/ The United States May Be Guilty of War Crimes in Yemen]. ''[[The Nation]].'' November 2016.\n*[http://www.tomdispatch.com/post/176220/tomgram%3A_rebecca_gordon%2C_yet_another_undeclared_u.s._war/ Tomgram: Rebecca Gordon, Yet Another Undeclared U.S. War] (December 2016), ''[[TomDispatch.com]]''\n*[https://fas.org/sgp/crs/mideast/R43960.pdf Yemen: Civil War and Regional Intervention] [[Congressional Research Service]]\n*[http://www.wsws.org/en/articles/2018/07/13/yeme-j13.html UAE and US guilty of war crimes in Yemen torture centers, Amnesty charges]. [[World Socialist Web Site]]. 13 July 2018\n*[https://www.the-american-interest.com/2018/10/04/ending-the-not-so-futile-war-in-yemen/ Ending the Not-So-Futile War in Yemen]. The American Interest. 4 October 2018\n\n{{Yemeni Civil War (2015)}}\n{{Middle East conflicts}}\n{{Ongoing military conflicts}}\n{{Post-Cold War Asian conflicts}}\n{{Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant}}\n{{Yemen topics}}\n{{Iran\u2013Saudi Arabia relations}}\n{{Iran\u2013United States relations}}\n{{Russia\u2013United States relations}}\n{{North Korea\u2013United States relations}}\n{{Armed conflicts involving the United States Armed Forces|state=collapsed}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Yemeni Civil War (2015-present)}}\n[[Category:Yemeni Civil War (2015\u2013present)| ]]\n[[Category:2010s civil wars]]\n[[Category:2015 in Yemen]]\n[[Category:Arab Winter in Yemen]]\n[[Category:Conflicts in 2015]]\n[[Category:Military history of Yemen]]\n[[Category:Ongoing conflicts]]\n[[Category:Shia\u2013Sunni sectarian violence]]\n[[Category:Wars involving Saudi Arabia]]\n[[Category:Wars involving the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant]]\n[[Category:Wars involving Yemen]]\n[[Category:Yemeni Crisis (2011\u2013present)]]\n[[Category:Iran\u2013Saudi Arabia proxy conflict]]\n[[Category:Iran\u2013United States proxy conflict]]\n[[Category:Human rights abuses]]\n", "name_user": "Neutrality", "label": "safe", "comment": "obvious from context", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yemeni_Civil_War_(2015%E2%80%93present)"}
{"title_page": "Alexander Hutchinson (Vermont)", "text_new": "'''Alexander Hutchinson''' (July 4, 1764 \u2013 February 25, 1853) was a [[Vermont]] [[politician]] who served as [[State Auditor]].\n\nHe was born in [[Grafton, Massachusetts]]. His siblings included [[Titus Hutchinson]].\n\nA lifelong bachelor, Hutchinson resided in [[Woodstock, Vermont]], where he became a successful merchant and had a reputation as an eccentric.<ref>U.S. Federal Census entry for Alexander Hutchinson, 1810</ref><ref>U.S. Federal Census entry for Alexander Hutchinson, 1850</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=24gKAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA115 Diary entry of Christopher C. Baldwin for April 15, 1831], published in Archaeologia Americana: Transactions and Collections of the American Antiquarian Society, Volume 8, 1901, pages 114 to 115</ref>\n\nHutchinson was a veteran of the [[American Revolution]], responding with other members of his [[militia]] unit in the aftermath of the [[Royalton Raid]].<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=TLETAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA31 A Biographical Sketch of the Rev. Aaron Hutchinson, A.M. of Pomfret, Vermont], by Rush Christopher Hawkins, 1888, page 31</ref>\n\nHe served in local offices, including Register of [[Probate]] and [[postmaster]].<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=Y4EUAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA490 History of Woodstock, Vermont], by Henry Swan Dana, 1889, page 490</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=KwMDAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA69 Official Postal Guide], published by U.S. Post Office Department, 1819, page 69</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=4iHiqHCs4ksC&pg=PA134 List of Post Offices in the United States], published by U.S. Post Office Department, 1828, page 134</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=y4MUAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA81 Catalogue of the Principal Officers of Vermont], by Leonard Deming, 1851, page 81</ref>\n\nFrom 1806 to 1813 and 1815 to 1817 Hutchinson was Vermont's State Auditor.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=g7c3AQAAIAAJ&pg=PA115 Records of the Governor and Council of the State of Vermont, entry for October 17, 1806], published by E.P. Walton, 1877, page 115</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=e4wUAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA381 Early History of Vermont], by LaFayette Wilbur, Volume 3, 1902, page 381</ref>\n\nHutchinson died in [[Pomfret, Vermont]].<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=TLETAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA31 A Biographical Sketch of the Rev. Aaron Hutchinson, A.M. of Pomfret, Vermont], by Rush Christopher Hawkins, page 31</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-off}}\n{{succession box | title=[[Vermont Auditor of Accounts]] | before= [[Benjamin Emmons|Benjamin Emmons, Jr.]]| after=[[Job Lyman]]| years=1806\u20131813}}\n{{succession box | title=[[Vermont Auditor of Accounts]] | before= [[Job Lyman]]| after=[[Willis Hall, Jr.]]| years=1815\u20131817}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hutchinson, Alexander}}\n[[Category:1764 births]]\n[[Category:1853 deaths]]\n[[Category:State Auditors of Vermont]]\n[[Category:People from Grafton, Massachusetts]]\n[[Category:People from Woodstock, Vermont]]\n[[Category:People from Pomfret, Vermont]]\n[[Category:People of Vermont in the American Revolution]]\n", "text_old": "'''Alexander Hutchinson''' (July 4, 1764 \u2013 February 25, 1853) was a [[Vermont]] [[politician]] who served as [[State Auditor]].\n\nHe was born in [[Grafton, Massachusetts]].\n\nA lifelong bachelor, Hutchinson resided in [[Woodstock, Vermont]], where he became a successful merchant and had a reputation as an eccentric.<ref>U.S. Federal Census entry for Alexander Hutchinson, 1810</ref><ref>U.S. Federal Census entry for Alexander Hutchinson, 1850</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=24gKAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA115 Diary entry of Christopher C. Baldwin for April 15, 1831], published in Archaeologia Americana: Transactions and Collections of the American Antiquarian Society, Volume 8, 1901, pages 114 to 115</ref>\n\nHutchinson was a veteran of the [[American Revolution]], responding with other members of his [[militia]] unit in the aftermath of the [[Royalton Raid]].<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=TLETAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA31 A Biographical Sketch of the Rev. Aaron Hutchinson, A.M. of Pomfret, Vermont], by Rush Christopher Hawkins, 1888, page 31</ref>\n\nHe served in local offices, including Register of [[Probate]] and [[postmaster]].<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=Y4EUAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA490 History of Woodstock, Vermont], by Henry Swan Dana, 1889, page 490</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=KwMDAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA69 Official Postal Guide], published by U.S. Post Office Department, 1819, page 69</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=4iHiqHCs4ksC&pg=PA134 List of Post Offices in the United States], published by U.S. Post Office Department, 1828, page 134</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=y4MUAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA81 Catalogue of the Principal Officers of Vermont], by Leonard Deming, 1851, page 81</ref>\n\nFrom 1806 to 1813 and 1815 to 1817 Hutchinson was Vermont's State Auditor.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=g7c3AQAAIAAJ&pg=PA115 Records of the Governor and Council of the State of Vermont, entry for October 17, 1806], published by E.P. Walton, 1877, page 115</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=e4wUAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA381 Early History of Vermont], by LaFayette Wilbur, Volume 3, 1902, page 381</ref>\n\nHutchinson died in [[Pomfret, Vermont]].<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=TLETAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA31 A Biographical Sketch of the Rev. Aaron Hutchinson, A.M. of Pomfret, Vermont], by Rush Christopher Hawkins, page 31</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-off}}\n{{succession box | title=[[Vermont Auditor of Accounts]] | before= [[Benjamin Emmons|Benjamin Emmons, Jr.]]| after=[[Job Lyman]]| years=1806\u20131813}}\n{{succession box | title=[[Vermont Auditor of Accounts]] | before= [[Job Lyman]]| after=[[Willis Hall, Jr.]]| years=1815\u20131817}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hutchinson, Alexander}}\n[[Category:1764 